Subtree of Another Tree
Easy
Given the roots of two binary trees root and subRoot, return true if there is a subtree of root with the same structure and node values of subRoot and false otherwise.

A subtree of a binary tree tree is a tree that consists of a node in tree and all of this node's descendants. The tree tree could also be considered as a subtree of itself.

 

Example 1:


Input: root = [3,4,5,1,2], subRoot = [4,1,2]
Output: true
Example 2:


Input: root = [3,4,5,1,2,null,null,null,null,0], subRoot = [4,1,2]
Output: false

Solution

class Solution {

    public boolean isIdentical(TreeNode root, TreeNode subRoot) {
        // Both are null -> structurally identical
        if (root == null && subRoot == null) {
            return true;
        }
        // One is null, the other isn't -> not identical
        if (root == null || subRoot == null) {
            return false;
        }
        // Values don't match -> not identical
        if (root.val != subRoot.val) {
            return false;
        }

        // Check both left and right subtrees
        return isIdentical(root.left, subRoot.left) && isIdentical(root.right, subRoot.right);
    }

    public boolean isSubtree(TreeNode root, TreeNode subRoot) {
        // An empty tree is always a subtree
        if (subRoot == null) {
            return true;
        }
        // If the main tree is empty but subRoot isn't, it can't be a subtree
        if (root == null) {
            return false;
        }

        // If the current nodes match, check if the trees are identical
        if (root.val == subRoot.val) {
            if (isIdentical(root, subRoot)) {
                return true;
            }
        }
        
        // If not identical at the current node, check the left and right children
        return isSubtree(root.left, subRoot) || isSubtree(root.right, subRoot);
    }
}
